Meadowood Napa Valley's Cashew Milk

6 c raw cashews
4-6 c water
4-6  medjool dates, pitted
1 vanilla bean, scraped
1 tbsp ground cinnamon
1/2 tsp sea salt

Cover cashews in water and soak for 6-8 hrs in the refrigerator. Strain out the water and place cashews in a blender along with the dates, vanilla, cinnamon, and sea salt. Add a cup of resh water at a time, blending the ingredients and adding more water until smooth and desired consistency is reached. Pass through a fine mesh sieve and refrigerate. Can keep for 2-3 days.


Note: keep remnants from straining, scoop into a ramekin, toss in some berries and eat like a pudding
